<sect1 id="templates_page_1templates_intro">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>AnalysisG uses a template-based design pattern where base template classes define the interface and common functionality, while user-defined subclasses implement analysis-specific logic.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="templates_page_1templates_inheritance">
<title>Inheritance Hierarchy</title>
<sect2 id="templates_page_1templates_event">
<title>Event Templates</title>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classtools" kindref="compound">tools</ref></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/>└──<sp/><ref refid="classevent__template" kindref="compound">event_template</ref></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>└──<sp/>UserDefinedEvent</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect2>
